Question: Develop an argument for or against using a cellphone while driving.
Answer:
Using a cell phone while driving is very reckless. When texting, one or both of your hands must leave the steering wheel, and your eyes leave the road. Bith of these things greatly reduce reaction time to any hazards. phone calls are a bit safer since you can still watch the road, but you still devote a hand and some of your attention to the phone rather than the changing road conditions.